<TEXT>
   Gunmen ambushed and killed the mayor
of a northern town, and Communist rebels raided a town in the
central Philippines over the weekend, officials reported Sunday.
   Mayor Romulo Liclican of Diffun in Quirino province died
immediately and his driver was injured in the shooting Saturday
morning, said reports from the Philippine Constabulary headquarters
and the official Philippine News Agency.
   The pair were ambushed as they drove past a village 140 miles
