said.
   Authorities could not immediately identify the suspects or
suggest a motive.
   On Samar island, about 200 New People's Army rebels raided the
Lorente town hall Friday and killed an employee, the military
reported. Samar is 380 miles southeast of Manila.
   Guerrillas searched houses for firearms and soldiers and fled
with five M-16 rifles, ammunition and radio equipment in stolen
vehicles, a police report said. It did not say why the government
employee was shot.
   The rebels have been fighting 20 years to establish a Marxist
state in the Philippines.
