<HEAD>Libya Accuses British of Chauvinism on Shakespeare Origins</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ROME (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The official Libyan news agency criticized the
British media Sunday for ridiculing Col. Moammar Gadhafi's
contention that William Shakespeare was of Arab origin.
   JANA, monitored in Rome, also said that any Arab ties to
Shakespeare would not increase Arab prestige but would be instead
``an honor to the British and Shakespeare himself and his family.''
   ``The smell of chauvinism seems to have overwhelmed the
atmosphere of the talk broadcast by the British radio on the
historical view regarding the attribution of the name of
Shakespeare to Arab origins, as put forward by brother Moammar
