others no civilized mind would accept.''
   The dispatch attributed the reports in the British media to ``a
very strong pressure of Zionist egoism which does not recognize the
right of others to freedom of expression.''
   Three British newspapers ridiculed Gadhafi for the assertion. A
fourth, The Daily Telegraph, described it as a joke that Gadhafi
had originally told the deputies of the Tunisian Parliament in
December.
