<HEAD>Wells Fargo Employees Would Quit Rather Than Work Saturdays</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SAN FRANCISCO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Nearly 300 Wells Fargo &amp; Co. employees have
told the bank they would quit instead of work new evening and
weekend hours, bank officials said.
   About 5 percent of the branch employees said they would quit
after the bank issued an ultimatum to 5,530 retail branch employees
stating that they must either work the new hours or leave the bank.
   Earlier this year, Wells Fargo expanded its hours. Branches are
now until 6 p.m. Monday through Friday and on Saturday from 9 a.m.
to 1 p.m. The bank previously stayed open until 4 p.m. on Monday
through Thursday and until 6 p.m on Friday, and was closed Saturday.
   The new hours require that employees work some evening hours and
Saturday shifts. However, they were not required to put in a longer
week.
